import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['home_score'] = pd.to_numeric(data['home_score'], errors='coerce')
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='home_score', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['home_score'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Mean Score: {:.2f}'.format(data['home_score'].mean()))
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of home scores?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['away_score'] = pd.to_numeric(data['away_score'], errors='coerce')
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='away_score', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['away_score'].median(), color='red', label='Median: {:.2f}'.format(data['away_score'].median()))
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of away scores?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['score_diff'] = data['score_diff'].astype(int)
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='score_diff', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['score_diff'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Mean Score Difference: {:.2f}'.format(data['score_diff'].mean()))
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of score differences?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['count'] = 1
    division_count = data.groupby('division')['count'].sum().reset_index()
    chart = sns.barplot(x='division', y='count', data=division_count)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of matches played in each division?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['team'] = data['home_team']
    data = data.append({'team': 'All', 'count': data['count'].sum()}, ignore_index=True)
    data = data.groupby('team').sum().reset_index()
    data = data.sort_values(by='count', ascending=False)
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(12, 6))
    sns.barplot(x='team', y='count', data=data, ax=ax)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of matches played by each team?', wrap=True)
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
